			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can think of several ways to balance pets:
<br />

<br />
 - Increase the effect of focus items.  Or even better, have a lot of focus items with varying effects that stack.  Maybe a melee damage effect, a damage mitigation effect, a damage avoidance effect, a hp increasing effect, a flurry/crit increasing effect, etc.
<br />

<br />
 - More pet increasing AAs.
<br />

<br />
 - Make the fire pet sing and dance.  It'd be more useful than what he does now.  Maybe give him a jester hat.
<br />

<br />
 - Don't make focused pets start with armor, have that be their base AC so we can then give them armor if we so choose (though I must concede it's nice not to have to summon that crap for my pet anymore).
<br />

<br />
 - An series of ancient spells that summon better pet toys, including armor, not just belts and weapons.
<br />

<br />
I'm not necessarily saying ALL of these should go in, but a combination of these things would be nice to see.  Also a base increase in damage and the such would be nice, but how much of an increase would depend on which of the above were implemented and how they were implemented.[/list][/list]</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
