			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We are looking at this from the wrong viewpoint. The pets need work, but not in the direction that most are taking. I feel that the Attack rating should be increased. I feel that the pets should represent their roles better. Fire should automatically /pet back off, /pet sit or /Pet guard to replinish mana and then nuke again. 
<br />

<br />
Air was deemed Monk because of its hit points and certain stats. Other than that you can call it whatever you like. 
<br />

<br />
If you want to affect pet balancing it needs to begin at the mage.  Better heals and a broader diversity of buffs would be a step in the right direction. I dont think it would be too much to ask for a pet only stat buff that is not associated with Burnout. Str, Dex, Agi. AC buffs for the pet would be a nice addition also. It is our direct influence on the pet that protects us that is lacking.
<br />

<br />
Instead of asking for a higher damage, why not ask to shorten the spread of damage that the pet can do? What is the point of asking for a pet that can hit for 150, if the spread is 25 min to 150 max? If you want a ripper of a pet ask for damage spread of 60 min to 100 max, or something to that effect. Pet consistancy would be real power.<br />_________________<br />Why do other classes argue about who can solo better? They are welcome to the camp as soon as I am done.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
