				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Very rarely post here but here's my thoughts. They basically stem from the philosophy that at the level a lot of us are at now (GOD/OOW), having our pet be able to tank mobs, i think, is not an option. and that the major issue we have is with our pets at a basic level, not the things we use to augment them (aa's items spells) .... note, all
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Air:</span> to me seems fine as is. hits for 110 with dpoc, love the stuns, love the proc rate, think it has sufficient hps.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Water:</span> again seems fine though being a higher level pet (to attain) i would like it to dish out marginally more damage than air in pure hit damage only. air hits for 110 with dpoc so i would not think it unreasonable for water to hit for say 115 with dpoc. its damage should reflect the level of its owner. that is the only change i would think to make to it.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Fire:</span> has a few problems currently, but can see possibilities for an awesome overhaul. problems being the debuffs it casts (annull/root) and the self buffs. this pet should come into existance pre buffed. it should not cast debuffs on mobs, period. it should be a nuke machine, so either needs to a) have its mana pool increased, or b) give it some BADASS nukes (non player nukes) that it will cast few and far between. differentiate it between a pet and a player. Another option for fire pet, is do away with the wizard aspect all together. make it a weak as melee pet, hit for say 70 with dpoc, but give it same hit points as air pet, and a massive innate DS, say 100pt. this would basically give us our "living DoT" pet back, as it would allow us to chain them and still bring a mob down. perhaps even lower its hps so we couldn't do those harder hitting mobs (make the hps low enough to make chaining not viable)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Earth:</span> this is the one i think the devs need to change the most. earth has long been considered a warrior pet. at this stage in the game, to be able to tank anything that hits for 500+ (wos/mpg/hell even tactics mobs) will make it over powered. my thinking on this one is 3 tiered. 1) lower its hitpoints, i dont think pet tanking in the above zones should be feasible (my opinion only). 2) increase its melee damage to represent that of the level required to attain it. it has always been the last to get (therefore needed to be the higest level) so make it hit for say 120 with dpoc. 3) here is the kicker, ditch the root proc in favour of a snare proc. this would give the mage an option to nuke kite mobs in open areas, asopposed to hoping that the nuke breaks root, and that your pet lasts long enough on the mob to have it be ble to root it. the snare would still attract a great deal of aggro from the mob, so the mage would need to be dishing out the damage to pull it fomr the pet. gives a chance to root-rot so to speak. and even if we cant pull aggro from pet and it dies to a barrage of 600 hits, at least the mob is snared and we have a chance of getting another pet out before being plastered across the scenery.
<br />

<br />
i realise the earth idea may be a little out there, but this pet is the pinnacle of mage pet-ness. especially the 70 one, as the rune to get it is no drop, and hard to get. it SHOULD be a game altering pet for our class.
<br />

<br />
my point is, they changed the "classes" of the pets before, i think it might be time to do it again. they just aren't viable with the new content coming out....<span style="font-weight: bold">in my opinion.</span>  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_think.gif" alt="Think" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Trixi Pixter
<br />
67 Mage - Southern Legion - Tribunal</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
