<br />

<br />
Do you mean pet, as in singular?  And I wouldn't classify 170 (got a link to that?  Highest I recall seeing is 140) as "approaching" 200, more like 185, but that's just semantics.
<br />

<br />
Earth/Air need further differentiation (woo, did I just make a word up?).  It's almost like we're down to 2 pets now, Earth/Air and Water.  You can lump two together because they're so close now, and nobody even uses another one.
<br />

<br />
Really, we should have 2 kinds of pets:  tanks, and DPS.  Fire/Water should be DPS, Fire doing the most because it has the worst HP and tanking (and it was highest DPS pre-50 anyway).  Earth should be the best tank, with the worst damage output, and decent at aggro holding.  Air should be a decent enough tank, less than earth, but do more DPS to compensate.
<br />

<br />
In fact, I like the concept of Fire/Water as different types of DPS (Spells vs Melee) so much, maybe I'd modify the Air pet to do elemental melee damage (give it innate weapons with like 70 Magic damage or something).  So if we find something with incredibly high AC, we can have the Air pet tank it and still do appreciable DPS via "magic melee."<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212730" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nirrudn Ak`Lmar</a>,
<br />
<a href="http://www.sok.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sterling Order of Knights</a>
