				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">my way of thinking is this, why do we need to have "tank" pets past 65? The content we would be looking at soloing/offtanking makes short work of PC tanks, let alone what we summon up, so why then should we expect to have a pet that is sturdy enough to tank it?
<br />

<br />
perhaps by tuning the pets we have post 65 to more of utility type pet, as opposed to the brutes many in our community are demanding they be, we can develop new strategies of becoming useful in a group, and more importantly in my eyes, on our own. YES our pets should be damage dealers, but to push consistenly, and often blindly, in this direction, may be to the detriment of our class overall.
<br />

<br />
with the advent of OoW and even GoD to a lesser extent (both sets which are aimed at 60+ characters) gone are the days when we can expect jabober to be our trusty meatshield. mobs just hit too hard and too fast.<br />_________________<br />Trixi Pixter
<br />
67 Mage - Southern Legion - Tribunal
<br />
"It could be worse."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
